  "texts": [
    "If g is an invariant metric on a twisted principal N-bundle π: M n → B d, with N unimodular, then,Ric g ( Û, Û) = Ric h (U, U) + |AU | 2 -1 2 τ (h)(U, U) + h(L H U, U), (16a) Ric g ( X, X) = Ric g B (X, X) -|L X | 2 -2 |A X | 2 + g B (∇ X H, X).",
    "(16b)Furthermore, when A = 0, we view h: B → Sym 2 + (𝔫 *), and it holds thatRic g ( Û, X) = tr adU L X, (17a) Ric g ( X, X) = Ric g B (X, X) -h * g sym ( X, X) + g B (∇ X H, X).",
    "(17b)Here X denotes the lift of X to B, and g sym is the symmetric metric on Sym 2 + (𝔫 *) (39).Proof.",
    "Locally, the geometry is that of a principal bundle with an invariant metric, thus (16)follows directly from [BL23a, Thm.",
    "2.2] and Lemma 2.18 below."
